<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7252] RingCache cannot be configured to use local DC only</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7252</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;RingCache always calls describe_ring, returning the entire cluster.  Considering it&apos;s used in the context of writing from Hadoop (which is typically in a multi-DC configuration), this is often not desirable behavior.  In some cases there may be high-latency connections between the analytics DC and other DCs.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I am attaching a patch that adds an optional config value to tell RingCache to use local nodes only, in which case it calls describe_local_ring instead.  It also adds helpful failed host information to IOExceptions thrown in AbstractColumnFamilyOutputFormat.createAuthenticatedClient, CqlRecordWriter, and ColumnFamilyRecordWriter.  This allows a user to more easily solve related connectivity issues.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
